<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1324,284,790]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis box="[312,435,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet derives from the Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[966,1036,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">flavus</emphasis>
” = yellow + 
<emphasis box="[1190,1244,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">tibia</emphasis>
, referring to the yellow hind tibia characteristic of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[312,1306,764,790]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
